            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for assisstance, `__import__()` indeed supports pyx. Here is my working code, for reference. I am generating a unique random module name, so no need for reloading.\r\n```py\r\n\r\nmodulename = \"construct_compile_target_\"+hexlify(os.urandom(8)).decode()\r\nimport pyximport\r\npyximport.install()\r\n\r\nwith open(modulename+\".pyx\", \"wt\") as f:\r\n    f.write(source)\r\nmodule = __import__(modulename)\r\nos.remove(modulename+\".pyx\")\r\n```",
